The paper discusses multi-antenna technologies and their application in wireless communication systems, which falls under the field of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of beamforming and massive MIMO also involves system-level simulations and optimization, which are relevant to the sub-categories of systems and control (cs.SY) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper mentions the spatial distribution of users, which could potentially involve natural language processing and text analysis (cs.CL).
